		<hr size="1">I don't think Tinkered Pets would harm the game at all. The Brazier of Elemental summoning does not. Some Ideas that I think would make the pet work for any Class:<P> 1. Tinkering is level dependent like research skill (as far as I've seen, or they could make it that way) Thus you would have to obtain Higher Levels to make better pets (the same way wizards must obtain levels to use higher level pet spells). <P>2. "Make them expensive to make and die when you zone", here is my idea on this point: Yes, make them progressivly more expensive to make (as spell scrolls are too buy). But the pet should not be destroyed completely, when you log or zone the pet should depower or power-down and go back into your inventory. To power it back up you need to install an expensive power source type module into the pet (like gems used as reagents in spells) The twist on this could be a check against your tinker skill to see if you suceed otherwise the reagent is lost for that try (thus preventing high level players "twinking" pets to newbies). Being able to keep the pet makes it kinda of like a spell but not quite; Spells take up no inventory and weigh nothing whereas pets take up slots and have weight.<P>3. Pet classes maybe? (I don't like this limiting idea but I'm just throwing them out) Rogues could Get pets that try to get behind a monster and try To Backstab it a level maybe 10 less than theirs? Fighters get a pet akin to that of SK, and casters get some kind of pets that casts debuff spells or whatever (ick don't like this idea)<P>4. Probably Limited global memory to have all kinds of Pets (what is it, 2 megs?) ; The spiders, male gnomes, female gnomes, the mechanical spiders.<P>If I sat down and really thought about this I'm sure I could write a great guidesheet to installing this into the game and making it a balanced addition to the the Tinker skill. I could have  a lot of fun with it. I just think all the Trade skills are fun in general. If verant had a one person working on each of trade skills full time I think they could have incredible depth. I am starting to get sick of the "Evercamp" part of the game but Had a real blast making jewerly to sell to other players. But that is becoming ruined now as the Loot in dungeons is Becoming VASTLY superior to many player made Items. Ok I'm just rambling now. There are some ideas.<P>-- Fleah Powder, Rogue of Xegony<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
